<HEADLINE>
OLIVIA NEWTON-JOHN TO PERFORM IN TAIPEI
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, March 16 (CNA) 03/16/07  19:37:15 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
Olivia Newton-John will give two concerts in Taipei when she
visits Taiwan for the first time in late April, organizers of the
events said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 58-year-old Australian singer, who had a string of pop hits
in the 1970s, is scheduled to perform in the Taipei Arena April
21-22 and treat her fans in Taiwan to a set of her greatest hits.
</P>
<P>
In a long-distance telephone interview with the CNA and ET Today,
a cable TV network and organizer of her Taipei concerts, Newton-
John said she looks forward to her tour of Taiwan and expects to
use the opportunity to savor various cuisines and local
delicacies.
</P>
<P>
After being told that Taiwan has very good health care services,
including acupuncture and other alternative medicines, Newton-
John -- a 15-year breast cancer survivor -- said she would be
interested in experiencing such services.
</P>
<P>
Taipei is the second leg of Newton-John's forthcoming Asian tour.
She will perform in Hong Kong April 15, in Shanghai April 24, in
Singapore April 27 and in Kuala Lumpur April 29.
</P>
<P>
Newton-John was born in England in 1948. Her family moved to
Australia when she was 5. She captured American hearts in the
mid-1970s with songs like "I Honestly Love You" and "Have You
Never Been Mellow." After winning a series of Grammy Awards for
her work, she settled in Malibu, near Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
She has also won numerous Country Music Awards, American Music
Awards and Peoples Choice Awards.
</P>
<P>
A versatile singer, Newton-John has covered rock songs as well as
the gentle folk songs and ballads which formed her early
repertoire.
</P>
<P>
She starred with John Travolta in the 1978 movie Grease and
catapulted herself into super-stardom with such great hits as
"You're The One That I Want," "Summer Nights" and "Hopelessly
Devoted To You."
</P>
<P>
In 1981, she reached the pinnacle of her career with her million-
selling single "Physical."
</P>
<P>
After recuperating  from breast  cancer  surgery  in 1992,
Newton-John became a staunch supporter of breast cancer awareness
charities and has been advocating early detection and treatment.
</P>
<P>
Her recent releases include her Indigo CD of 2004 -- a tribute to
the women singers who influenced her in the early days of her
career; Stronger Than Before -- a CD of life-affirming songs with
proceeds going to breast cancer awareness -- and a healing CD
"Grace and Gratitude" in 2005.
</P>
